He says the graduates must create new opportunities for inclusive sustainable development. JOHANNESBURG - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa has called on graduates at the University of Mpumalanga to become national assets of the country.He says the graduates must create new opportunities for inclusive sustainable development.Ramaphosa was speaking at the institution s first graduation ceremony since its inception three years ago.He attended the ceremony in his capacity as the chancellor of the university.Ramaphosa says graduates can now challenge the world. You will be robed with knowledge and kept with wisdom. And you ve become part of the league of educated people in our country for the rest of your lives. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)